<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="527" pageId="3" pageNumber="526" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1885,2020]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1436,151,249]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="527" pageId="3" pageNumber="526">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1885,1911]" pageId="3" pageNumber="526">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wang, Yang &amp; Wei" authorityYear="2015" box="[680,773,1885,1911]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Haphsa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="526" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lueta">
<emphasis box="[680,773,1885,1911]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="526">H. lueta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the body size and mesonotum markings, but it can be distinguished from the latter by the shape of the uncal lobes (lateral uncal lobes broad and developed, parallel to each other in 
<taxonomicName authority="Wang &amp; Peng &amp; Wei, 2021" authorityName="Wang &amp; Peng &amp; Wei" authorityYear="2021" box="[307,468,1957,1983]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Haphsa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="526" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acutipetala" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[307,468,1957,1983]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="526">H. acutipetala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[476,541,1957,1983]" pageId="3" pageNumber="526">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[476,541,1957,1983]" pageId="3" pageNumber="526" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
; lateral uncal lobes long, gradually narrowed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wang, Yang &amp; Wei" authorityYear="2015" box="[1094,1186,1957,1983]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Haphsa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="526" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lueta">
<emphasis box="[1094,1186,1957,1983]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="526">H. lueta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and the much longer opercula. This new species is also similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1850" box="[649,804,1993,2019]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Dundubia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="526" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nicomache">
<emphasis box="[649,804,1993,2019]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="526">H. nicomache</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the length of opercula, i.e., both extending to the posterior margin of sternite VI, but it can be distinguished from the latter by the shape of opercula and the basal lobes of pygofer in male (basal lobes of pygofer thin, opercula with pointed apices in 
<taxonomicName authority="Wang &amp; Peng &amp; Wei, 2021" authorityName="Wang &amp; Peng &amp; Wei" authorityYear="2021" box="[1039,1199,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Haphsa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="527" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acutipetala" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1039,1199,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="527">H. acutipetala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1206,1269,187,213]" pageId="4" pageNumber="527">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1206,1269,187,213]" pageId="4" pageNumber="527" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
; basal lobes of pygofer broad, opercula with rounded apices in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1850" box="[688,843,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Dundubia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="527" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nicomache">
<emphasis box="[688,843,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="527">H. nicomache</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
